{"title":"SRAM HS2 MTB Brake Rotor gets new Brake Track and Thermal Dissipating Paint","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/01/sram-hs2-mtb-brake-rotor-gets-new-brake-track-and-thermal-dissipating-paint/","date":1630505471000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div data-off-canvas-content=\"\"><main role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-270066\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><header></header><section itemprop=\"text\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095636/LesGets21_o2a4563.jpg\"><figure><img width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095636/LesGets21_o2a4563.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs%3Adevice%2Frscb28-1\" alt=\"\" loading=\"eager\" data-feature=\"1\" srcset=\"\" sizes=\"\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\"><figcaption>UCi MTB WC, DH and XCO, Les Gets, France</figcaption></figure></a><p>Want better braking? Of course you do. If it’s a matter of simply running a better rotor for improved performance, sign us up. That’s what SRAM is claiming to offer with their newest brake rotor, the HS2.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095643/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_07_7261_L.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095643/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_07_7261_L.jpg\" alt=\"SRAM HS2 brake rotor\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095643/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_07_7261_L.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095643/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_07_7261_L-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095643/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_07_7261_L-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095643/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_07_7261_L-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095643/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_07_7261_L-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095643/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_07_7261_L.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095643/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_07_7261_L.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095643/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_07_7261_L-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095643/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_07_7261_L-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095643/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_07_7261_L-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095643/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_07_7261_L-768x512.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>Meant specifically for mountain biking, the HS2 claims to offer 7% better power. That increase comes from things like a new brake track design that is said to “increase pad traction.” It looks like it would also be quieter as well.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095645/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_10_7286_L.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095645/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_10_7286_L.jpg\" alt=\"rounded edge of brake rotor\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095645/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_10_7286_L.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095645/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_10_7286_L-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095645/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_10_7286_L-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095645/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_10_7286_L-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095645/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_10_7286_L-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095645/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_10_7286_L.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095645/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_10_7286_L.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095645/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_10_7286_L-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095645/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_10_7286_L-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095645/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_10_7286_L-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095645/SM_210111_NewG2finishes_Studio_Harookz_10_7286_L-768x512.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>The rotor itself is now thicker at 2.00mm, which when combined with the special heat dissipating paint, leads to a rotor that runs cooler when compared to the previous Centerline model. According to SRAM’s testing in Garda, the new HS2 rotor ran up to 40°C cooler. Additionally, the edges of the rotors are rounded.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095631/005018176003-AM-DB-ROTORBOLTS-HS2-220-ROUNDED-c-Side.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095631/005018176003-AM-DB-ROTORBOLTS-HS2-220-ROUNDED-c-Side.jpg\" alt=\"6-bolt SRAM HS2 brake rotor\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1200\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095631/005018176003-AM-DB-ROTORBOLTS-HS2-220-ROUNDED-c-Side.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095631/005018176003-AM-DB-ROTORBOLTS-HS2-220-ROUNDED-c-Side-297x297.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095631/005018176003-AM-DB-ROTORBOLTS-HS2-220-ROUNDED-c-Side-800x800.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095631/005018176003-AM-DB-ROTORBOLTS-HS2-220-ROUNDED-c-Side-120x120.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095631/005018176003-AM-DB-ROTORBOLTS-HS2-220-ROUNDED-c-Side-768x768.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01095631/005018176003-AM-DB-ROTORBOLTS-HS2-220-ROUNDED-c-Side-125x125.jpg 125w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" 